1276
01:15:39,880 --> 01:15:43,880
 Before we open up our floor for our Q&A session,

1277
01:15:43,880 --> 01:15:47,880
 where you can actually scan the code or use the mic in the middle, like I said,

1278
01:15:47,880 --> 01:15:52,880
 I would like to ask Dr. Philip and see if you have anything to respond.

1279
01:15:52,880 --> 01:15:57,880
 But fortunately, despite Dr. Liu was speaking Cantonese,

1280
01:15:57,880 --> 01:16:02,880
 we have utilized AI to help us translate his manuscript into English,

1281
01:16:02,880 --> 01:16:05,880
 so Dr. Philip could understand.

1282
01:16:06,880 --> 01:16:09,880
 I'd like to say thank you very much for the response,

1283
01:16:09,880 --> 01:16:12,880
 and I'll use some of these tools.

1284
01:16:12,880 --> 01:16:17,880
 I think that I love the way that you made the point

1285
01:16:17,880 --> 01:16:21,880
 that AI is a quick fix for many things.

1286
01:16:21,880 --> 01:16:23,880
 It's an easy way to get knowledge.

1287
01:16:23,880 --> 01:16:26,880
 It's an easy way to find out information.

1288
01:16:26,880 --> 01:16:29,880
 But is it there in the long run?

1289
01:16:29,880 --> 01:16:33,880
 I love the idea of not getting a call from--

1290
01:16:33,880 --> 01:16:38,880
 you know, AI won't get the call in the middle of the night to the hospital.

1291
01:16:38,880 --> 01:16:44,880
 AI won't get the call to support somebody who has cancer.

1292
01:16:44,880 --> 01:16:48,880
 Yeah, that whole kind of sense of the longevity of preaching ministry,

1293
01:16:48,880 --> 01:16:52,880
 of pastoral ministry, absolutely crucial.

1294
01:16:52,880 --> 01:16:57,880
 That AI, that digital culture, is often a quick fix,

1295
01:16:57,880 --> 01:17:00,880
 but we're in it for the long term with people,

1296
01:17:00,880 --> 01:17:02,880
 living with them in their daily lives.

1297
01:17:02,880 --> 01:17:08,880
 And we really need to do better than going to a quick fix machine.

1298
01:17:08,880 --> 01:17:10,880
 Yeah?

1299
01:17:10,880 --> 01:17:14,880
 Yes.

1300
01:17:14,880 --> 01:17:18,880
 And I think there is a difference between British culture

1301
01:17:18,880 --> 01:17:22,880
 and Hong Kong culture about that,

1302
01:17:22,880 --> 01:17:25,880
 because I think sometimes--

1303
01:17:25,880 --> 01:17:28,880
 my experience of being here for the first time

1304
01:17:28,880 --> 01:17:32,880
 is that food is very quick and--

1305
01:17:32,880 --> 01:17:34,880
 (laughter)

1306
01:17:34,880 --> 01:17:38,880
 quickly sourced, quickly eaten, and you go on to the next thing,

1307
01:17:38,880 --> 01:17:42,880
 rather than spending a long time cooking a meal

1308
01:17:42,880 --> 01:17:47,880
 and sharing the meal and eating the meal and digesting the meal.

1309
01:17:47,880 --> 01:17:51,880
 And I just wonder whether there's a difference there

1310
01:17:51,880 --> 01:17:53,880
 between what I'm saying about--

1311
01:17:53,880 --> 01:17:56,880
 what we're saying about the quick fix of AI,

1312
01:17:56,880 --> 01:18:02,880
 and the long-term need for digesting God's Word.

1313
01:18:02,880 --> 01:18:06,880
 So yeah, thank you so much. It's superb.

1314
01:18:06,880 --> 01:18:08,880
 Thank you.

1315
01:18:08,880 --> 01:18:12,880
 So we'll have some questions through WhatsApp,

1316
01:18:12,880 --> 01:18:15,880
 or you can use the mic in the middle.

1317
01:18:15,880 --> 01:18:17,880
 So I've got a quick question.

1318
01:18:17,880 --> 01:18:20,880
 So a question to Dr. Philip.

1319
01:18:20,880 --> 01:18:24,880
 You used the 2010 polling from Durham University.

1320
01:18:24,880 --> 01:18:27,880
 It's now 2026.

1321
01:18:27,880 --> 01:18:30,880
 How do you think it has changed in the last 16 years,

1322
01:18:30,880 --> 01:18:34,880
 and how much is it related to technology development,

1323
01:18:34,880 --> 01:18:38,880
 including things that are not limited to AI?

1324
01:18:38,880 --> 01:18:40,880
 Especially--

1325
01:18:40,880 --> 01:18:42,880
 Testing.

1326
01:18:42,880 --> 01:18:45,880
 Especially on the point what people are looking for in a sermon.

1327
01:18:45,880 --> 01:18:47,880
 Yeah.

1328
01:18:47,880 --> 01:18:53,880
 So one of the things that I was interested in,

1329
01:18:53,880 --> 01:18:57,880
 what Michael said, was that

1330
01:18:57,880 --> 01:19:00,880
 the rush towards information--

1331
01:19:00,880 --> 01:19:03,880
 Everything's quick, as I said, about food and everything.

1332
01:19:03,880 --> 01:19:05,880
 Everything's very, very quick.

1333
01:19:05,880 --> 01:19:07,880
 But--

1334
01:19:07,880 --> 01:19:09,880
 And in a way, that is--

1335
01:19:09,880 --> 01:19:11,880
 That's what distraction culture is all about.

1336
01:19:11,880 --> 01:19:14,880
 Everything's fast. Everything's this, this, this, this.

1337
01:19:14,880 --> 01:19:16,880
 Get on to the next bit.

1338
01:19:16,880 --> 01:19:21,880
 But I think-- But I'm not too sure that's quite right.

1339
01:19:21,880 --> 01:19:24,880
 Movies have got longer.

1340
01:19:24,880 --> 01:19:27,880
 Concerts have got longer.

1341
01:19:27,880 --> 01:19:30,880
 Experiences have got longer.

1342
01:19:30,880 --> 01:19:34,880
 But there's a slow process in digitality

1343
01:19:34,880 --> 01:19:38,880
 that we're kind of missing if we think it's all quick fix.

1344
01:19:38,880 --> 01:19:43,880
 And so when you hear Jordan Peterson speaking,

1345
01:19:43,880 --> 01:19:45,880
 it's for hours and hours and hours.

1346
01:19:45,880 --> 01:19:49,880
 Or Charlie Kirk, or, you know, just about anybody.

1347
01:19:49,880 --> 01:19:53,880
 There's that kind of longevity about what's happening.

1348
01:19:53,880 --> 01:19:55,880
 Yes, TikTok is all over,

1349
01:19:55,880 --> 01:19:58,880
 and Facebook is all over in a second kind of thing.

